metadata.name: Dune, But Water World
metadata.description:
1/1 featuring [Jiorgi](https://instagram.com/lilsabotage)

Shot in the evening in Miami.  I love being there. 

This was the last outing for my acrylic dome port because I fell off a breakwater climbing down into the water and scratched the hell out of it.  Jiorgi had to drive me to a CVS afterwards due to a shocking amount of bleeding I was experiencing from contact with the barnacles on the breakwater during my tumble.

Image details below:
-Created 07/28/2018 in Miami, FL
-Shot on Nikon d850 with Nikkor 16-35 inside of a
Nauticam housing with a 180mm acrylic dome port
-4000px long edge

More about this collection [Here](https://damonloblephotography.com/they-went-overboard)

My most up to date images are always on my [Insta](https://instagram.com/damonloble) and [Twitter](https://twitter.com/olnikkormat)
